# Styling with twrnc

## Import

Always import the shared `tw` instance — never create a new one:

```ts
import tw from '~configs/tw';
```

## No Inline Styles

Never write inline style objects directly on JSX elements:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — inline style object
<View style={{ flex: 1, backgroundColor: 'white', padding: 16 }} />
<Text style={{ fontSize: 14, color: '#111827', fontWeight: '600' }} />

// ✅ GOOD — tw template literal
<View style={tw`flex-1 bg-white p-4`} />
<Text style={tw`text-sm text-gray-900 font-semibold`} />
```

If a value cannot be expressed as a Tailwind class, move it to `StyleSheet.create` (see below) — never leave it inline.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — non-Tailwind value left inline
<View style={{ backgroundColor: 'rgba(0,0,0,0.5)' }} />

// ✅ GOOD — extracted to StyleSheet
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  overlay: { backgroundColor: 'rgba(0,0,0,0.5)' },
});
<View style={styles.overlay} />
```

## Basic Usage

```tsx
// ✅ Template literal for static classes
<View style={tw`flex-1 bg-white p-4`} />

// ✅ tw.style() for conditional/merged classes
<View style={tw.style('flex-1', isActive && 'bg-primary')} />

// ✅ Array to combine tw + StyleSheet
<View style={[tw`rounded-2xl`, styles.sheet]} />
```

## Device Context

Call `useDeviceContext(tw)` once in `useAppBootstrap` — never in individual components:

```ts
// src/hooks/useAppBootstrap.ts
useDeviceContext(tw);
```

## When to Use StyleSheet.create

Only for values **not expressible** as Tailwind classes:

```ts
// ✅ Acceptable — rgba overlay, percentage heights
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  overlay: { backgroundColor: 'rgba(0,0,0,0.5)' },
  sheet: { maxHeight: '70%' },
});

// ❌ Do NOT use StyleSheet for standard spacing, colors, or flex values
```

## Custom Colors

The only custom color is `primary: '#1E40AF'` — use `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, etc.
Add new custom colors in `tailwind.config.js` under `theme.extend.colors`.

## Dark Mode

Dark mode class is controlled via `[data-mode="dark"]`. Apply dark variants with:

```tsx
<View style={tw`bg-white dark:bg-gray-900`} />
```
